               <msContents>
                  <summary>I)Maṣḥafa lǝdätu la-ʾabuna Takla Hāymānot “Book of the Genealogy of
                     ʾabuna Takla Haymanot” (fols. 4ra-5ra)&#xD; - Genealogy of Takla Hāymānot
                     (fols. 4ra-5ra)&#xD; II) Gadla Takla Hāymānot “Vita of Takla Haymanot” (fols.
                     5ra-94vb)&#xD; III) Bǝʿǝlä nagaśt "Riches of the Kings" (fols. 95ra-98ra)&#xD;
                     IV) Taʾāmra Takla Hāymānot “Miracles of Takla Haymanot”: 20 miracles (fols.
                     98ra-107vb)&#xD; &#xD; Additio 1.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The text of the Vita represents the first of the two sub-types of the
                        Dabra Libānos recension of the Gadla Takla Hāymānot (close, but not
                        identical to the published text of the Vita, s. E.A.W. BUDGE (ed., tr.), The
                        Life and Miracles of Takla Hâymânôt in the Version of Dabra Lîbânôs...,
                        London 1906).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
